  Locus:
    Date: 20 August 2017
    Chapter: 8
  Copyright: 2002
  Translator: Douglas Allchin
---
Utmost virtue, how like water.
Water gives all creatures life
and flows in lowly places,
ever closer to the Way.

Dwell lowly.
Respect deeply.
Trust freely.
Govern justly.
Work authentically.
Act upon opportunity.

Who does not contend
is free of contention.
